post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_19541086_19541301_0": {"length": 14, "quality": 0.9333333333333333, "section_id": 7067}}, "n3337": {"so_19541086_19541301_0": {"length": 14, "quality": 0.9333333333333333, "section_id": 6811}}}, "19541301": {"PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>It means, that <code>extern \"C\"</code> should be only in namespace-scope (not class-scope, block-scope etc.) Something, that is not in namespace, but is in global scope - is in global namespace scope.</p>\n<p><blockquote><p id=\"so_19541086_19541301_0\">\nThe potential scope denoted by\nan original-namespace-name is the concatenation of the declarative regions established by each of the\nnamespace-definitions in the same declarative region with that original-namespace-name.\n</p></blockquote></p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2013-10-23T12:10:27.797", "Id": "19541301", "CommentCount": "0", "CreationDate": "2013-10-23T12:10:27.797", "ParentId": "19541086", "Score": "1", "OwnerUserId": "1498580"}, "19541086": {"ViewCount": "1065", "Body": "<p>The C++ spec (<a href=\"http://www.open-std.org/jtc1/sc22/wg21/docs/papers/2011/n3242.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.open-std.org/jtc1/sc22/wg21/docs/papers/2011/n3242.pdf</a>, section 7.5.4) states that</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_19541086_19541086_0\">A linkage-speci\ufb01cation shall occur only in namespace scope</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>What exactly does \"namespace scope\" mean? Does this mean that a linkage-specification, such as <code>extern \"C\"</code> can't be in global scope, only in a namespace?<br>\nWhat exactly does \"namespace scope\" mean?</br></p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "19541301", "Title": "C++ \"namespace scope\"", "CreationDate": "2013-10-23T12:00:29.907", "Id": "19541086", "CommentCount": "0", "FavoriteCount": "0", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastActivityDate": "2013-10-23T12:10:27.797", "Score": "1", "OwnerUserId": "331785", "Tags": "<c++><namespaces><extern><specifications>", "AnswerCount": "1"}});